A [new music video](https://vimeo.com/39875998 "One Day on Earth Music Video")
has been released in preparation for the[ worldwide
screening](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2012/02/22/one-day-on-earth-global-
screening-of-pioneer-worldwide-collaborative-film/ "worldwide screening of One
Day on Earth via Global Voices") of the Global Collaborative film One Day on
Earth, which will take place in locations all around the planet on Earth Day
(22 April, 2012). The video features musicians, poets and dancers captured on
film all during the same 24 hour period in 10 October, 2010, artfully recut
and remixed by Cut Chemist.

> The collaborative film [One Day on Earth](http://www.onedayonearth.org/ "One
> Day on Earth site") was filmed all on the same day, October 10, 2010, with
> more than 3,000 hours of footage sent in from all corners of the world,
> showcasing the amazing diversity, conflict, tragedy, and triumph that occurs
> in one day. The [Global Screening](http://www.onedayonearth.org/screening
> "One day on earth screening") will take place on Earth Day (April 22, 2012)
> in every country of the world, with the assistance of World Heritage Sites
> and the United Nations.

The music video includes footage from India, Papua New Guinea, Benin, Burkina
Faso, USA, China, North Korea, Mongolia, Kenya, Afghanistan, Jamaica, Spain,
Taiwan and many other locations.

You can read more about the upcoming screening on our previous post [_One Day
on Earth: Global Screening of Worldwide Collaborative
Film_](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2012/02/22/one-day-on-earth-global-
screening-of-pioneer-worldwide-collaborative-film/ "GV post on One Day on
Earth") and you can sign up for a screening in your city or town on the [One
Day on Earth](http://www.onedayonearth.org/screening "One Day on Earth sign-up
for screening event") site.

